OL,3,C'Real concerns' about the workings of
OL,4,CJersey's construction industry
OL,6,FThe investigation identified a clear
OL,7,Fneed for more effective competition in
OL,8,Fthe industry, saying that limited
OL,9,Fconsumer choice, rising costs, and
OL,10,Fstructural issues threaten the
OL,11,Fsector's resilience and sustainability.
OL,13,FIt found that residential property
OL,14,Fowners are concerned about a lack of
OL,15,Fcompetition and limited choice of
OL,16,Fcontractors, resulting in high prices
OL,17,Fand inefficient project delivery.
OL,19,FThe report also found that costs in
OL,20,FJersey tend to be higher than in other
OL,21,Fjurisdictions.
