OL,3,C'Real concerns' about the workings of
OL,4,CJersey's construction industry
OL,6,FThese high prices are driven by
OL,7,Flogistical and transport difficulties,
OL,8,Fconcentrated market structures, labour
OL,9,Fcosts and productivity levels.
OL,11,FFinally, the JCRA identified four
OL,12,Ffurther "markets of interest" where a
OL,13,Flack of competition is resulting in
OL,14,Fsectors functioning poorly.
OL,16,FThese were:
OL,18,FThese three markets will be further
OL,19,Finvestigated by the JCRA to ensure
OL,20,Fanti-competitive practices such as
OL,21,Fprice-fixing are not taking place.
